# Development Agreement

Produces a comprehensive owner-developer development agreement for a real estate project with clear scope, timeline, and risk allocation.

## Prerequisites

1. Parties and authority: legal names, entity types, signatory authority, addresses.
2. Property details: legal description, parcel numbers, zoning, current condition.
3. Project scope: project type, size, quality standards, exclusions.
4. Delivery model: design-bid-build, design-build, developer-as-manager, etc.
5. Pricing model: fixed, GMP, cost-plus, fee structure, contingency.
6. Schedule: target dates, milestone list, critical path assumptions.
7. Permits and entitlements: responsibility split, known approvals needed.
8. Insurance and risk allocation: required coverages and limits.
9. Exhibit list: plans, specs, budget, schedule, forms, notices.

## Output Structure / Process

### Intake Table

| Item | Required Inputs | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Parties | Legal names, entity types, authority | Add licensing if required |
| Property | Legal description, APN, address | Attach as exhibit |
| Project | Type, size, quality standards | Include exclusions |
| Plans | Approved plans list | Define approval path |
| Budget | Base budget, contingency, allowances | Specify currency |
| Price model | Fixed/GMP/cost-plus, fee | Define cost categories |
| Schedule | Milestones, completion dates | Define excusable delays |
| Permits | Responsibility split | Include entitlements |
| Insurance | Types and limits | Additional insureds |
| Dispute forum | Court or arbitration | Venue and rules |

### Required Definitions

| Term | Definition Standard |
| --- | --- |
| Project | Scope, location, intended use |
| Plans | Approved plans and change process |
| Milestone | Objective criteria for completion |
| Substantial Completion | Functional use standard |
| Final Completion | Punch list cleared, closeout |
| Change Order | Written, signed change |
| GMP/Cost-Plus | Cost categories and fee |
| Force Majeure | Events and notice |
| Permits | Required approvals list |

### Core Agreement Sections

| Section | Must Include | Drafting Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Recitals | Property, purpose, prior studies | No promises |
| Scope of Work | Design, permitting, construction | Attach scope exhibit |
| Developer Duties | Management, quality control | Standard of care |
| Owner Duties | Access, approvals, funding | Cooperation obligations |
| Schedule | Milestones, deadlines | Time is of essence |
| Pricing | Model, cost definition | Audit rights if cost-plus |
| Payments | Draws, retainage | Lien waivers |
| Change Orders | Process and pricing | Written approval |
| Warranties | Workmanship, code compliance | Duration |
| Insurance | CGL, WC, builders risk | Additional insureds |
| Indemnity | Mutual, negligence-based | Exclude gross negligence carveout as needed |
| IP | Ownership and license | Design professional rights |
| Confidentiality | Scope, term, exceptions | Subcontractor flowdown |
| Permits | Responsibility split | Stop-work remedies |
| Termination | For cause and convenience | Cure periods |
| Disputes | Negotiation, mediation, forum | Fees and costs |
| Boilerplate | Notices, assignment, survival | E-signatures |

### Milestone Schedule Template

| Milestone | Target Date | Completion Criteria | Approval |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Design Development | TBD | Owner approval of plans | Written |
| Permit Submission | TBD | Filed applications | Copy to owner |
| Permit Issuance | TBD | Permits issued | Evidence |
| Construction Start | TBD | Notice to proceed | Written |
| Substantial Completion | TBD | CO or equivalent | Owner signoff |
| Final Completion | TBD | Punch list closed | Closeout package |

### Payment Terms Template

| Payment Type | Trigger | Documentation |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Mobilization | Execution/NTP | Insurance certs |
| Progress Draw | % complete or milestone | Lien waivers, reports |
| Retainage | Withhold % | Release at final |
| Final Payment | Final completion | All closeout items |

### Change Order Procedure

1. Written change request with scope, cost, and schedule impact.
2. Owner approval deadline and deemed response rule.
3. No work on change without signed change order except emergency.
4. Approved change adjusts price and schedule.

### Exhibits Checklist

- Exhibit A: Property legal description.
- Exhibit B: Scope and specifications.
- Exhibit C: Approved plans list.
- Exhibit D: Baseline schedule.
- Exhibit E: Budget and cost categories.
- Exhibit F: Insurance requirements.
- Exhibit G: Payment application and lien waiver forms [VERIFY].
- Exhibit H: Notice addresses.

## Guidelines

- Use the property’s state for governing law and venue unless negotiated.
- If entitlements are required, allocate who leads zoning or variance efforts.
- Tie schedule remedies to excusable vs. inexcusable delays with notice rules.
- Liquidated damages must be reasonable estimates of actual loss.
- Retainage and lien waivers often have statutory form or timing rules [VERIFY].
- Make confidentiality survival explicit (3-5 years or trade secret standard).
- Ensure indemnity does not violate anti-indemnity statutes [VERIFY].
- If recording is contemplated, confirm local recording format and notarization rules [VERIFY].
